  , issueCommentBody =
      "I think this is probably the problem: https://github.com/rethinkdb/rethinkdb/blob/next/drivers/javascript/net.coffee#L1041\r\n\r\nIn my compiled JS from the published module, the line says to emit 'close', not 'error':\r\n\r\n```js\r\n    this.rawSocket.on('error', (function(_this) {\r\n      return function() {\r\n        var args;\r\n        args = 1 <= arguments.length ? __slice.call(arguments, 0) : [];\r\n        if (_this.isOpen()) {\r\n          _this.close({\r\n            noreplyWait: false\r\n          });\r\n        }\r\n        return _this.emit('close');\r\n      };\r\n    })(this));\r\n```\r\n\r\nSo it appears to have been published before 3c1a642, which would have fixed this, was merged.\r\n\r\nIndeed, patching this section to read\r\n\r\n```js\r\n    this.rawSocket.on('error', (function(_this) {\r\n      return function(err) {\r\n        var args;\r\n        args = 1 <= arguments.length ? __slice.call(arguments, 0) : [];\r\n        if (_this.isOpen()) {\r\n          _this.close({\r\n            noreplyWait: false\r\n          });\r\n        }\r\n        return _this.emit('error', err);\r\n      };\r\n```\r\n\r\ncorrects the behavior, causing the error to propagate as expected."
  , issueCommentId = 75356265
